<topic template="Default" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">Accessing Environment Variables</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword translate="true">Accessing Environment Variables</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Accessing Environment Variables</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Environment variables are frequently used in conjunction with command line applications, and can be read as using the </text><text styleclass="Class Name" translate="true">getenv</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">() function of the CRT. For example:</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">CRTLibrary default getenv: &apos;TZ&apos;</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The result is a </text><text styleclass="Class Name" translate="true">String</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> (in this case the name of the current timezone).</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">New environment variables can be added, the value of existing variables changed, or variable removed, using the </text><text styleclass="Class Name" translate="true">_putenv</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">()</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> function. </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">CRTLibrary default _putenv: &apos;Dolphin=Cool&apos;.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><text styleclass="Code Example" translate="true">CRTLibrary default getenv: &apos;Dolphin&apos;</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">See Microsoft&apos;s documentation for further details of </text><text styleclass="Class Name" translate="true">_putenv</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">()</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">.</text></para>
  </body>
</topic>
